Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.48,0:01:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing on Lotte's mind ever since she returned \Nfrom Munich is "Dad and Frau Gerlach - what's going on?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.72,0:01:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually so liable to despondency, Lotte did not expect \NHerr Gabele, living next door, to reignite her determination.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.58,0:02:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,While conferring with the kind Herr Gabele about a matter \Nso painful to her, Lotte couldn't help breaking into tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.82,0:02:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,However, through crying heartily, \Nshe managed to bring her feelings in order,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.75,0:02:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing Lotte to come up with a new, \Neven more ingenious plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.22,0:02:20.22,Sign,,0,0,110,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 21 \N {\fs35} Dad, Don't Get Married! {お父さん結婚しないで} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.44,0:02:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like me to leave them here, Herr Palfy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.19,0:02:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.05,0:02:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my... Could I be possibly \Ndistracting you too much, from your job?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.71,0:02:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, no! You're... Oh, wow! \NThose flowers are majestic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.52,0:02:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,My... Then, I guess, I must start \Nbringing you flowers every morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.33,0:02:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.13,0:03:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The one thing more striking than flowers here, \Nis you, Frau Irene.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.95,0:03:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Don't you want \Nto take a few minutes break?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.84,0:03:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.74,0:03:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.98,0:03:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.77,0:03:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, good morning to you, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.12,0:03:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.13,0:03:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I have...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.79,0:03:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! If you have a visitor, \NI'll go prepare some tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.15,0:03:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My, she sure keeps you under her thumb. \NIt's as if she was your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.57,0:03:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm amazed myself at how briskly \Nshe picked up this thoughtfulness. {unsure how to wrap this: these days, strangely/miraculously/skillfully, with briskly; quickly; promptly she is to be thoughtful; to be tactful; to be sensitive} {it's "She's been acting lately in a very determined way, and what she does is absolutely right—so what can I do?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.54,0:03:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, the summer camp this year\Nexerted the most beneficial influence on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.11,0:03:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good observation, \Nkids her age make rapid steps towards independence. {no fucking clue what she means by "kids increasingly outside" maybe "... need to meet new people" or "spend a lot of time away from home" or "are going more and more on their own adventures"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.67,0:03:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But a constant overprotection, like that of yours,\Nmay seriously hamper the process. {overprotective; excessive care; overprotection; overprotectiveness}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.69,0:04:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My overprotection? \NBut I'm just doing what a father should...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.28,0:04:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If a father exerts an excessive influence on his child, {/affects too much}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.72,0:04:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the latter ends up developing a father complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.22,0:04:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning that even in the future \Nshe won't be able to stand on her own feet. {being independent; becoming independent}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.48,0:04:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.10,0:04:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. Sorry I kept you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.10,0:04:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.51,0:04:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, while we're at it, Luise, \N are you here for a purpose? {/you have any business}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.04,0:04:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.24,0:04:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Then please don't pay me no mind. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.22,0:04:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, do you know the painter who lives next door to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.83,0:04:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? Herr Gabele, right? I know the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.43,0:04:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well he is my friend, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.80,0:04:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And, well... Today I'm going to his place \Nto let him sketch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Very glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.44,0:04:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,About that... You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.74,0:04:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting a bit difficult for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.97,0:05:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The room where Herr Gabele lives \Nhas tiny windows that don't let through enough light.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, he would have liked a more spacious room \Nwith lots of light coming from above!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.56,0:05:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, it could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.27,0:05:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like this room, exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.53,0:05:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I guess he ought to find \Na more accommodating atelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.67,0:05:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's... What I thought, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the vacant ateliers \Nare not thick on the ground, he says...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.24,0:05:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly is this girl's play? {/trying to say}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.58,0:05:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought this,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.48,0:05:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to do the composing, you don't really need a room like this, \Nwith a lot of light coming from above, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I guess that sounds about right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.96,0:05:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So well... I put two and two together \Nand thought this -
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.39,0:05:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,if dad and Herr Gabele
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.39,0:05:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,exchange rooms, \Nwouldn't it be better?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.93,0:05:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, Herr Gabele would have \Nan atelier with all the light he needs!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.83,0:05:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd be making good paintings!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.47,0:05:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And dad would also be working right next to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.50,0:06:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd even be able \Nto come home for dinner every time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.11,0:06:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day, I would be making your favorite...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.55,0:06:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, even when you are working, I'll be able to hear \Nyour piano, so I... won't feel so... lonely...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.70,0:06:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I hope you both excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.40,0:06:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy, I shan't distract you any longer. {not sure what she means, seems to be just a snobbish way to say "excuse me" - "A respectful expression that expresses apology for bad manners or inconvenience to the other party . It is an elegant, polite and elegant way of speaking that is often used by women of good families" but I suspect asobase may imply I'll leave you playing around}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.01,0:06:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... But... Frau Irene!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.51,0:06:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Frau Irene? \NI thought we're dining together tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.82,0:06:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? But won't you be too preoccupied \Nwith moving to a new place now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.76,0:06:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.09,0:06:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't take her words seriously, do you? {/this girl proposed an impossible thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.73,0:06:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If this keeps up, \Nrumors will start spreading like wildfire. {no clue what she means: at this rate, people will say }
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.42,0:06:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You should consider taking a slipper \Nto your daughter, sometimes. {/punish her on the butt}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.77,0:06:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't hesitate to take a firm stand - \Nthat's what all the fathers do. {/be more fatherly and resolute}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.96,0:07:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.87,0:07:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That girl will learn not to meddle in grownups' affairs. {to interrupt; to interfere; to meddle; to intrude; to butt in; to poke one's nose into}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.83,0:07:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be sure to tell her off a bit. {lit: let's do a bit of attention/care/precaution/warning/admonishment/reprimand so I hope he just means "I'll talk to her about it"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.54,0:07:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If you wish the best for Luise, \Nthat's exactly what you ought to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.57,0:07:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, it's enough for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.41,0:07:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad seems irritated...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.59,0:08:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Still more work to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.16,0:08:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you... coming home to supper?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.87,0:08:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I want you to listen closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.34,0:08:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like it when other people \Ndeliver me any unnecessary worry. {in book: I don't like other people interfering with my affairs, not even my own daughter!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.68,0:08:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it's my daughter Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.42,0:08:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What's good for me and what's not - \NI can very much figure it out for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.99,0:08:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.49,0:08:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.90,0:08:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.84,0:08:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,She looked distressed, \Nbut this all is for Luise's own good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.39,0:09:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What a brazen girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.85,0:09:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite being just a brat, she tries to manipulate \Nand monopolize Herr Palfy, by keeping him on a short leash!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.29,0:09:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not having it your way.  {i hope this is what she means by "it won't go this way"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.92,0:09:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't hesitate to accept your challenge, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.31,0:09:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein, are you not feeling well enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.45,0:09:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't even touched your meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.46,0:09:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm all right, Resi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe just a little extra tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.36,0:09:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go to bed early today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.73,0:09:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say so. \NWell, sweet dreams then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.93,0:09:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was a brilliant idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.80,0:09:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.77,0:09:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad refused to even consider it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.90,0:09:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is disheartening beyond possible. {to be disappointed; to be dejected; to be downhearted; to be discouraged; to be disheartened; to lose heart; to feel let down}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.99,0:10:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any business here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.89,0:10:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me... My dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.17,0:10:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Irene, we got a visitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.63,0:10:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.87,0:10:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Just some Fraulein whom I don't know. {idk what she means by "from someplace I don't know"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.14,0:10:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But I am Luise! Luise, madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.65,0:10:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That girl is not Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.72,0:10:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad? But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.83,0:10:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.46,0:10:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I really am...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't lie, you know you aren't Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.91,0:11:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.38,0:11:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.75,0:11:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Peperl!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.64,0:11:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.77,0:11:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It came! Finally came!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.77,0:11:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Herr.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.00,0:11:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the joy that those letters give you, \Nthat makes my work worth doing! {something worth doing; something worthwhile} {unsure what he means by "the giving/handing over side/person"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.32,0:11:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A painter that lives next door?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.26,0:12:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I came up with an idea which is oh so bright!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.59,0:12:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Please pray that my plan works, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.61,0:12:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make sure they swap, whatever it takes! {really unsure if by "change/exchange/move" she means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.54,0:12:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite an undertaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.78,0:12:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte sure is giving it her best.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,On my part, I'm not let her down either! Alright! {/I won't lose}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.83,0:12:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.79,0:12:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.49,0:12:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous to read while walking!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.08,0:12:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So who is it you're not letting down?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.98,0:12:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.85,0:12:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a letter from a friend I met at the summer camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.92,0:12:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In it, she wishes me the best of luck \Nin improving my grades.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.79,0:12:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, I'm not...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.43,0:12:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, best of luck, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.11,0:12:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, \NI was mighty lucky to meet you here. {/we met at just the right place}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.97,0:12:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My work for today is done and dusted with.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.68,0:12:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say if we go eat somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.91,0:12:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds great!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.54,0:12:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, heavenly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.12,0:12:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The work was a breeze, \Nthe dinner was a feast. {/work went well, meal was delicious}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.02,0:12:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.01,0:12:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.63,0:13:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly happy, mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.39,0:13:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte is with me! Together, we lead a carefree life - \Nthat alone is enough for me to be happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.17,0:13:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, mom, suppose your could "re-bear" me, \Nwould you prefer me to get born as a boy instead? {she says otoko no hito instead of ko here and idk if there's any reason to that}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.88,0:13:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Or would you rather still have a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.84,0:13:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If I could "re-bear" you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.21,0:13:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's me think... \NI wouldn't mind having a boy either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.75,0:13:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But I guess, a girl is still preferable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.95,0:13:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A child such as Lotte, \NI would gladly "re-bear." {/I want to give birth to a child like lotte}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.52,0:13:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, should you meet my dad again, \Nwould you remarry him, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.34,0:13:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What's this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.53,0:13:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you'd need {\i1}my{\i0} dad and {\i1}my{\i0} mom \Nto "re-bear" me, wouldn't you? {/it was because there were dad and mom that I was born}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.63,0:13:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. That makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.91,0:13:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If... it would avail the present day me to "re-bear" you... {no clue what she means by "if, the way I am now, I could re-bear", a huge stretch, but my chain of logic is "I was a girl when I married him, so I may have had wrong expectations, so if I could re-bear you again, yes, for that, maybe remarrying him isn't bad (implying lotte's birth was the reason of marriage, not the consequence), but now we're experienced old people and we know what to expect of marriage and of each other, so we're in the good age for marriage and also I liked it so if your birth was the reason for marriage the first time, now I'm prepared to marry in order to give birth to you, but alas, you can't erase the mistakes of the past and we don't know if your dad still feels the same about me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.54,0:13:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Remarrying doesn't sound bad at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.77,0:13:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"Present day you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.01,0:14:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time I married your dad, \NI was still just a girl, barely out of the nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.75,0:14:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But as of now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.46,0:14:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,...Now you know how to make it work? {really hope she means this, not "but now you're experienced and adult so you know what to expect/legally allowed to enter the marriage"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.86,0:14:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, nobody knows for sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.28,0:14:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is supposing \Nyour dad hadn't changed either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.83,0:14:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, whatever. This had already happened, \Nand there's no overwriting it! {no clue what she means by "even though this story/talk can't be helped", maybe "what's the point of discussing what you couldn't help?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.23,0:14:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's return!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.37,0:14:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In real life, you can't just erase events \Nwith a piece of rubber!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.61,0:14:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But mom, you don't necessarily have to erase it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.38,0:14:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just turn the page to a clean one \Nand start writing anew.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.79,0:14:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.56,0:14:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What, need my hand now? {amaete? spoiled/childish?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.43,0:14:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.38,0:15:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.13,0:15:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbecoming of a girl \Nto look so pensive for a week straight. {it was "look like a rainy weekend" in book}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.50,0:15:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Did someone in school \Nsay a nasty thing about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.02,0:15:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing of the kind so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.82,0:15:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's call it here for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.30,0:15:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.30,0:15:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To drive out that rainy mood, \Nhow about we go out on a stroll for a tasty cake?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.31,0:15:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Herr Gabele.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.25,0:15:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Gabele, the cakes here are a terrible rip-off!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.57,0:15:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the better time for squandering than this? {lavish (use of something); abundant; copious; wasteful/luxury}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.05,0:15:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.57,0:16:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.11,0:16:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Been quite some time \Nsince you last visited me, Frau Irene. {act. he says "we havent seen for a while" but in the episode it doesn't feel like they did so w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.11,0:16:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I forget to shave somewhere? {/something stuck on my face?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.27,0:16:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.57,0:16:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Just trying to remember your face, \Nwhile I still have the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.08,0:16:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly do you mean to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.11,0:16:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, I'm leaving for America.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.35,0:16:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,With a good chance, I might never return.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.09,0:16:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To America?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.30,0:16:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's so out of the blue...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.53,0:17:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going there to marry someone. {/received a proposal}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.82,0:17:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone my father knows really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.07,0:17:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Marry?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.97,0:17:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.37,0:17:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.47,0:17:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"Congratulations," you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.77,0:17:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,My, how cruel!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.11,0:17:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Irene...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.35,0:17:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all you got to say? {/you're not supposed to say that}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.12,0:17:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Even knowing perfectly well \Nabout my feelings towards you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.15,0:17:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what father told me, {no fucking clue, may be "dad told me" maybe "I talked to dad" - no relation to adjacent lines}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.00,0:17:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"Herr Palfy is a man of arts, \Ntherefore he is too fickle and noncommittal. {no clue why choose such strange wording, clearly dad wouldn't be so verbose about palfy for no reason; this whole sentence is a mouthful that makes little sense: with palfy, who is a person who loves freedom for the sake of art - I also don't see why he should forbid this marriage since none of those qualities are bad}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.25,0:17:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, my dear, \Nbut this marriage is not coming true." {/you'll have to give up on}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.66,0:17:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like that. {/therefore}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.82,0:17:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, Frau Irene...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.19,0:17:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So harsh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.86,0:17:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Our time together was short, \Nbut I enjoyed every minute of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.40,0:17:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Even becoming a mother for little Luise \Nno longer seemed such a distant dream, and still... {unsure, most likely she means "there were even times when I saw dreams about ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.27,0:17:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll remember you as the best thing \Nthat happened to me, forever... {/will remember you in good words, definitely}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.39,0:18:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In your memories, I'll probably remain an egoist, \Nto whom the music was more important than anything. {not a clue what's omoidedanante, I suspect either "not just in memories" or "but please make sure, that for that picture in your memories"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.50,0:18:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, please remember, \Nthat you were equally as important to me. {I still don't know if it's supposed to be in the past or in the future, or in the present}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.56,0:18:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But you never really came \Nto feel any true need in me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.67,0:18:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.11,0:18:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We both do - both me and Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.88,0:18:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Irene,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.94,0:18:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to be my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.55,0:18:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.08,0:18:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm struggling to even believe my ears right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.55,0:18:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to marry you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.26,0:18:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.19,0:18:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.86,0:18:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my... What am I doing... {/should I do/answer}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.99,0:18:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you excuse me \Nfixing my makeup for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.61,0:18:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Said it out loud, at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.49,0:19:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Seized it at last. \NA complete success!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The final victory is mine, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.73,0:19:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, welcome home, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.30,0:19:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Resi. Doing groceries?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.70,0:19:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll be out just for a moment... I'll be... back...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.80,0:19:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, dad? \NThis something you wanted to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.38,0:19:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.85,0:19:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When me and your mom were, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.08,0:19:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we split ways, \NI've been completely alone all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.19,0:19:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,For seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.86,0:19:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, naturally, you've also been here with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.51,0:19:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.70,0:19:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.50,0:20:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In short, I'm introducing some changes into our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.11,0:20:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.08,0:20:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.71,0:20:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again, I... \NOr well... I've decided to get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.40,0:20:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's with Frau Irene Gerlach!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.33,0:20:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.67,0:20:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do this... You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.50,0:20:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't!..
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.80,0:20:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get married!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.67,0:20:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you, dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.61,0:20:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get married!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.36,0:20:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.68,0:20:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.55,0:20:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't you think \Nyou'll be happier, having a mother? {/luise herself wants a mom, doesn't she}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.12,0:20:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm quite certain, Frau Gerlach \Nwould make a wonderful mother for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.16,0:20:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing! You'll love it yourself, \Nas soon as our new life starts! {/get used to your new life/being}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.72,0:20:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you, and therefore, I have faith in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.02,0:20:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.80,0:20:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.70,0:21:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to be at the Opera House \Nfor a dress rehearsal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.04,0:21:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.25,0:21:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Above anything else, \Nthis house requires a proper mother. {/our family needs}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.65,0:21:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that, don't you, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.90,0:21:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.54,0:21:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.80,0:21:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Alas, the time had come \Nfor the worst nightmare to come true. {/finally, the thing more dreadful is happening}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.44,0:21:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Father made up his mind \Non marrying Frau Irene Gerlach. {/says he'll}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.71,0:21:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon hearing of this, Lotte felt \Nher whole body becoming as cold as ice. {/heart freezing to glacier}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.22,0:21:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It even took her some time to be able to move again.
Comment: 0,0:22:04.52,0:22:04.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.46,0:22:13.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.99,0:22:17.45,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.45,0:22:21.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.17,0:22:24.08,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.30,0:22:35.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.72,0:22:39.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.48,0:22:43.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.02,0:22:46.42,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.86,0:22:49.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.44,0:22:52.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.99,0:22:57.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.54,0:23:01.69,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.24,0:23:06.89,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.89,0:23:10.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.30,0:23:13.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.93,0:23:16.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.75,0:23:21.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.52,0:23:24.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:23:28.52,0:23:28.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.68,0:23:30.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.78,0:23:34.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,What should I do now, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.88,0:23:36.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something happened, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.55,0:23:41.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,I'm sure, something disastrous must have stricken Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.39,0:23:43.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,Will I be able to prevent this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.66,0:23:47.86,Sign,,0,0,0,,Please make sure you stop Frau Gerlach \Nand dad from marrying!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.86,0:23:49.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,I cannot allow this! {/object}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.70,0:23:51.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,Just wait till I tell him personally!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.86,0:23:54.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.27,0:23:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte's in Danger!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.13,0:23:58.53,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 22 \NLotte's in Danger!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.94,0:23:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
